modules.description: Parses TOML v0.4.0 formatted text into an abstract syntax tree representing key-value pairs, arrays, and tables. Processes strings, integers, floats, booleans, and datetime values embedded in structured configurations. Used to load and validate configuration files for applications requiring structured data input.

Converts TOML data into OCaml values using a custom decoder, handling errors gracefully. Operates on TOML value tables and nested structures. Used to parse configuration files into typed records during application startup.
